Dear @Eva zu Beck, I'm reminded of a quote I once heard from, The Secret Life of Walter Mitty. "Sometimes, if I like the moment; I mean me, I don't like the distraction of the camera." Individuals such as yourself and others in the same light are influential. Though, I believe those of us, who feel this internal drive to explore the vast diverse world around us, would not be able to ignore this drive inside us, regardless of the influencers. I'm left with this dilemma, of whether or not I should capture my experience on a camera or keep it entirely to my person. Would you say there has ever been a time where, you felt the camera took away from your experience or the authenticity of the travels, of the moment?
